  ('40', 'ROPE, CABLE, CHAIN, FITTINGS', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4010', 'CHAIN AND WIRE ROPE', '1978-10-15', null, 'Chain and Wire Rope', 'Bead Chain; Weldless Chain; Single Leg Chain Assemblies; Wire Rope; Wire Cord; Single Leg Wire Assemblies.', 'Power Transmission Chain (FSC 3020); Slings.', 'Chain and wire rope, with attachments or terminations will be classified in this class when they are for general use. a. Chain is a series of flexible links and/or rings fitted into one another used for supporting, lifting, restraining, dragging, or transmitting power. b. Wire rope is formed from strands of twisted wire.', '40 - ROPE, CABLE, CHAIN, FITTINGS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.3', 'Hardware & Tools'),
  ('4020', 'FIBER ROPE, CORDAGE, AND TWINE', '1978-10-15', null, 'Fiber Rope, Cordage, and Twine', 'Fibrous Cord Assemblies; Fibrous Cord; Fibrous Rope; Fibrous Twine.', 'Wire Rope (FSC 4010); Slings (FSC 3940).', 'Fiber rope is classified in this class when it is bulk material or for general use. Items with attachments and/or terminations are identified in this class unless a more specific item name is used. a. Fiber rope is flexible twisted strands of manila, nylon or other fiber. b. Cordage is ropes or cords used in rigging (see item name definitions for parameters). c. Twine is two or more strands twisted together.', '40 - ROPE, CABLE, CHAIN, FITTINGS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.3', 'Hardware & Tools'),
  ('4030', 'FITTINGS FOR ROPE, CABLE, AND CHAIN', '1978-10-15', null, 'Fittings for Rope, Cable, and Chain', 'Anchor Guys; Wire Stranded Bands; Wire Rope Clamps; Cargo Hooks; Shackles; Swivels; Rope Terminals; Rope Wedges.', 'Clamp Blocks (FSC 5340); Support Hooks (FSC 5340).', 'All items, including specially designed, will be classified in this FSC. Fittings classified in this FSC are items used in conjunction with chain, rope, and are attached to perform certain functions, (e.g., hooks, shackles, and wedges) refer to item name definitions for parameters.', '40 - ROPE, CABLE, CHAIN, FITTINGS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.3', 'Hardware & Tools'),
  ('41', 'REFRIG, AIR CONDIT/CIRCULAT EQPT', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4110', 'REFRIGERATION EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Refrigeration Equipment', 'Grocery Type Display Cases; Ice Cream Cabinets; Drinking Fountains (except portable and stationary types classified in class 4510); Professional and Scientific Refrigerators; Rivet Coolers; Photographic Refrigerators; Mortuary Refrigerators; Household and Commercial Refrigerators; Grocery Type Showcases; and other types of refrigeration equipment of the commissary or food store type.', 'Cafeteria Type Refrigerated Display Cases; Soda Fountains; Milk, Soda, and/or Ice Cream Dispensers; Cold Food Counters; Carbonators; Combination Heated-Refrigerated Food Serving Equipment; Cafeteria Type Showcases; Chilling Equipment used for display and serving of food (see class 7310 for these items). Also excluded from this class are refrigeration components (see class 4130).', 'This class includes only complete refrigeration equipment, whether refrigerated from an integral or remote mechanical refrigeration unit or system. Also included in this class are refrigeration plants, and complete "packaged" refrigeration units and systems containing a power driven compressor, condenser, evaporator, and all other necessary components to refrigerate an enclosed space. Nonoperating accessories such as ice trays, shelves, and panels are included in this class. Excluded from this class are operating components, assemblies, parts, attachments, or accessories, for use in or on complete refrigeration equipment, plants, systems, or the "packaged" refrigeration units, and which are to be classified in class 4130, or as otherwise specifically prescribed by the indexes and structure of the FSC.', '41 - REFRIG, AIR CONDIT/CIRCULAT EQPT', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4120', 'AIR CONDITIONING EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Air Conditioning Equipment', 'Store Type Units; Window and Room Type Units; Marine, and Vehicular Air Conditioning Units; Air Conditioning Plants and Systems.', 'Air Conditioning Components (FSC 4130, or as otherwise specifically prescribed by the indexes and structure of the FSC).', 'This class includes only complete air conditioning equipment, systems, and plants. Also included are specially designed nonoperating accessories such as a window panel used with a window type air conditioning unit to facilitate mounting. Excluded from this class are operating components, assemblies, parts, attachments, or accessories for use in or on air conditioning equipment, which are to be classified in FSC 4130, or as otherwise specifically prescribed by the indexes and structure of the FSC.', '41 - REFRIG, AIR CONDIT/CIRCULAT EQPT', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4130', 'REFRIGERATION AND AIR CONDITIONING COMPONENTS', '2011-10-01', null, 'Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Components', 'Heat Exchanger Equipment; Refrigerant Strainers; Refrigeration Compressors; Air Conditioning and Refrigeration Servicing Equipment, such as Charging and Testing Manifolds, Lines and Units; Operating Components of Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Equipment, Plants, and Systems classified in classes 4110 and 4120.', 'Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Plants (see classes 4110 and 4120): Collections of Refrigeration Components "packaged" as a unit including a refrigeration compressor, condenser, evaporator, etc., specifically designed and tailored for applications such as walk-in type refrigerators. Individual components of the "packaged" unit will be classified in class 4130, or as otherwise specifically prescribed by the indexes and structure of the FSC. The complete "package" unit will be classified in class 4110.', null, '41 - REFRIG, AIR CONDIT/CIRCULAT EQPT', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4140', 'FANS, AIR CIRCULATORS, AND BLOWER EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Fans, Air Circulators, and Blower Equipment', 'Wall Type Fans; Pedestal Type Fans; Household Type and Attic Type Exhaust Fans; Floor Fans; Forced Draft Exhaust and Disposal Kits; Fans; Air Circulators, and Blower Equipment, whether designated as "industrial" or "nonindustrial" by application and/or use.', 'Combination Heater-Fans (see FSC 4520).', 'Fans and impellers which are specifically designed for use with specific individual types of equipment are to be classified in the same classes as their next higher assemblies or in the appropriate components or accessories classes (as in group 25 or 29 or class 1680) as prescribed by the indexes and structure of the FSC.', '41 - REFRIG, AIR CONDIT/CIRCULAT EQPT', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4150', 'VORTEX TUBES AND OTHER RELATED COOLING TUBES', '2011-10-01', null, 'Vortex Tubes and Other Related Cooling Tubes', 'Tool Grinding spot coolers; machining spot coolers; electronic equipment spot coolers; and electronic cabinet spot coolers.', 'Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Plants (Classes 4110 and 4120); Air Conditioning Components and Cooler Unit, Air (Class 4130); Cooler, Air, Evaporative (Class 4120) and Pipe and Tube (Group 47).', null, '41 - REFRIG, AIR CONDIT/CIRCULAT EQPT', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('42', 'FIRE/RESCUE/SAFETY; ENVIRO PROTECT', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4210', 'FIRE FIGHTING EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Fire Fighting Equipment', 'Fire Extinguishers; Fire Axes; Fire Rakes; Fire Beaters; Fire Trucks; Fire Hose; Play Pipes; Hose Fittings having one or more Fire Hose End Connections; Fire Hose Reels; Fire Fighting Trailers; Fire Hydrants; Sprinkler Heads.', 'Wrecking Bars (FSC 5120, 1385).', null, '42 - FIRE/RESCUE/SAFETY; ENVIRO PROTECT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.2', 'Fire/Rescue/Safety/Environmental Protection Equipment'),
  ('4220', 'MARINE LIFESAVING AND DIVING EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Marine Lifesaving and Diving Equipment', 'Diving and Salvage Apparatus, including Pressurized Divers Suits; Rescue Nets, Buoyant; Inflatable Life Vests; Life Rafts.', 'Lifesaving Boats (FSC 1940).', null, '42 - FIRE/RESCUE/SAFETY; ENVIRO PROTECT', null, '14.0', 'Sustainment S&E', '14.2', 'Engines, Components & Spt Eq'),
  ('4230', 'DECONTAMINATING AND IMPREGNATING EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Decontaminating and Impregnating Equipment', null, null, 'Excludes production type equipment designed for impregnation of metal castings and electronic components, processing of leather and textiles, and for similar industrial processing operations.', '42 - FIRE/RESCUE/SAFETY; ENVIRO PROTECT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.2', 'Fire/Rescue/Safety/Environmental Protection Equipment'),
  ('4235', 'HAZARDOUS MATERIAL SPILL CONTAINMENT AND CLEAN-UP EQUIPMENT AND MATERIAL', '2011-10-01', null, 'Hazardous Material Spill Containment and Clean-up Equipment and Material', 'Secondary Spill Containment Sumps; Liquid Spill Containment Pallets; Spill Containment Basins; Spill Containment Systems; Absorbent, Sorbent and Blotting Materials.', null, null, '42 - FIRE/RESCUE/SAFETY; ENVIRO PROTECT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.2', 'Fire/Rescue/Safety/Environmental Protection Equipment'),
  ('4240', 'SAFETY AND RESCUE EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Safety and Rescue Equipment', 'Portable Fire Escapes; Safety Nets, Nonbuoyant.', 'Divers'' Suits; Fixed Fire Escapes', null, '42 - FIRE/RESCUE/SAFETY; ENVIRO PROTECT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.2', 'Fire/Rescue/Safety/Environmental Protection Equipment'),
  ('4250', 'RECYCLING AND RECLAMATION EQUIPMENT', '1991-10-01', null, 'Recycling and Reclamation Equipment', 'Material and Machinery designed to remove, neutralize and/or prepare for possible reuse of substances otherwise considered to be un-reclaimable.', null, null, '42 - FIRE/RESCUE/SAFETY; ENVIRO PROTECT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.2', 'Fire/Rescue/Safety/Environmental Protection Equipment'),
  ('43', 'PUMPS AND COMPRESSORS', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, 'This group excludes pumps and compressors designed for use on individual types of equipment, such as engine fuel pumps, aircraft propeller feathering pumps, fork lift operating pumps, compressors for operating gun turrets, and vehicular brake system compressors. Also excluded are items specially designed as or for use on fuel dispensing equipment. The FSC indexes and structure will govern the classification of these items permitted classification in a single class only.', null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4310', 'COMPRESSORS AND VACUUM PUMPS', '1978-10-15', null, 'Compressors and Vacuum Pumps', 'Truck Mounted and Trailer Mounted Compressors.', 'Refrigeration Compressors (FSC 4130).', null, '43 - PUMPS AND COMPRESSORS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4320', 'POWER AND HAND PUMPS', '1978-10-15', null, 'Power and Hand Pumps', 'Laboratory Jet Pumps (FSG 65 and 66).', 'Laboratory Jet Pumps (FSG 65 and 66).', null, '43 - PUMPS AND COMPRESSORS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4330', 'CENTRIFUGALS, SEPARATORS, AND PRESSURE AND VACUUM FILTERS', '2011-10-01', null, 'Centrifugals, Separators, and Pressure and Vacuum Filters', 'Laboratory Centrifuges (FSG 65 and 66); Water Purification Filters (FSC 4610).', 'Laboratory Centrifuges (FSG 65 and 66); Water Purification Filters (FSC 4610).', null, '43 - PUMPS AND COMPRESSORS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('44', 'FURNACE/STEAM/DRYING; NUCL REACTOR', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4410', 'INDUSTRIAL BOILERS', '1978-10-15', null, 'Industrial Boilers', 'Steam Boilers, over 15 pounds WSP; Marine Boilers; Boiler Drums; Water Heaters, Low Pressure (over 100 gallon recovery capacity).', null, null, '44 - FURNACE/STEAM/DRYING; NUCL REACTOR', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4420', 'HEAT EXCHANGERS AND STEAM CONDENSERS', '2011-10-01', null, 'Heat Exchangers and Steam Condensers', null, null, null, '44 - FURNACE/STEAM/DRYING; NUCL REACTOR', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4430', 'INDUSTRIAL FURNACES, KILNS, LEHRS, AND OVENS', '2011-10-01', null, 'Industrial Furnaces, Kilns, Lehrs, and Ovens', 'Crucible Furnaces; Cupola Furnaces.', 'Food Industry Ovens (FSC 7310); Metal Heat Treating Furnaces (FSC 3424); Laboratory Type Furnaces (FSC 6640).', null, '44 - FURNACE/STEAM/DRYING; NUCL REACTOR', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4440', 'DRIERS, DEHYDRATORS, AND ANHYDRATORS', '2011-10-01', null, 'Driers, Dehydrators, and Anhydrators', 'Evaporators.', null, null, '44 - FURNACE/STEAM/DRYING; NUCL REACTOR', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4460', 'AIR PURIFICATION EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Air Purification Equipment', 'Electronic Precipitators; Dust Collection Equipment.', 'Fan and Blower Equipment (FSC 4140); Air Conditioning Equipment (FSC 4120).', null, '44 - FURNACE/STEAM/DRYING; NUCL REACTOR', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4470', 'NUCLEAR REACTORS', '1978-10-15', null, 'Nuclear Reactors', 'Refueling Machines; Ion Chamber Seals; Thermal Barriers; Control Rods; Steam Generators, Pressurized Water; Reactor Vessel Shells; Handling Carts, Hoisting Units, New and Spent Cartridges.', null, 'This class includes all types of nuclear reactors and those items which are specifically designed for use within nuclear reactors, their primary cooling systems, auxiliary fluid systems, special propulsion plant systems, handling and servicing equipment, electrical and control systems, and associated special test and water chemistry control items. Excluded from this class are those items for which more specific classifications are suitable.', '44 - FURNACE/STEAM/DRYING; NUCL REACTOR', null, '11.0', 'Aircraft, Ships/Submarines & Land Vehicles', '11.3', 'Ships & Submarines'),
  ('45', 'PLUMBING, HEATING, WASTE DISPOSAL', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4510', 'PLUMBING FIXTURES AND ACCESSORIES', '1978-10-15', null, 'Plumbing Fixtures and Accessories', 'Bathtubs; Commodes; Lavatories; Shower Cabinets; Sinks; Water Closets; Accessories and Component Parts, such as Dispensers, Faucets, Holders, Racks, Shower Heads, Flush Valves and Stop Valves.', 'Fittings and Specialties for Hose, Pipe and Tube (FSC 4730).', null, '45 - PLUMBING, HEATING, WASTE DISPOSAL', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4520', 'SPACE AND WATER HEATING EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Space and Water Heating Equipment', 'Boilers, 15 pounds WSP and under (for boilers over 15 pounds WSP, see FSC 4410); Domestic Water Storage Tanks through 100 gallon capacity; Fireplace Heaters; Furnaces; Space Heaters; Heating Radiators; Immersion Heaters; Water Heaters, through 100 gallon recovery capacity (for heaters over 100 gallons recovery capacity, see FSC 4410).', 'Vehicle Heaters (FSC 2540); Aircraft Heaters (FSC 1660).', null, '45 - PLUMBING, HEATING, WASTE DISPOSAL', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4530', 'FUEL BURNING EQUIPMENT UNITS', '1978-10-15', null, 'Fuel Burning Equipment Units', 'Oil Burners; Stokers; Gas Burners.', null, null, '45 - PLUMBING, HEATING, WASTE DISPOSAL', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4540', 'WASTE DISPOSAL EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Waste Disposal Equipment', 'Compactors; Destructors; Garbage Disposals; Incinerators; Septic Tanks.', null, null, '45 - PLUMBING, HEATING, WASTE DISPOSAL', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('46', 'WATER PURIFICATION/SEWAGE TREATMENT', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4610', 'WATER PURIFICATION EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Water Purification Equipment', 'Demineralizers; Filtration Equipment; Ice and Snow Melters.', 'Water Purification Compounds (FSC 6810 and 7930); Water Softening Compounds (FSC 6810 and 7930).', null, '46 - WATER PURIFICATION/SEWAGE TREATMENT', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4620', 'WATER DISTILLATION EQUIPMENT, MARINE AND INDUSTRIAL', '2011-10-01', null, 'Water Distillation Equipment, Marine and Industrial.', 'Laboratory Distillation Apparatus (FSC 6640).', 'Laboratory Distillation Apparatus (FSC 6640).', null, '46 - WATER PURIFICATION/SEWAGE TREATMENT', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('4630', 'SEWAGE TREATMENT EQUIPMENT', '1978-10-15', null, 'Sewage Treatment Equipment', null, null, null, '46 - WATER PURIFICATION/SEWAGE TREATMENT', null, '4.0', 'Facilities & Construction', '4.3', 'Facility Related Materials'),
  ('47', 'PIPE, TUBING, HOSE, AND FITTINGS', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4710', 'PIPE, TUBE AND RIGID TUBING', '1978-10-15', null, 'Pipe, Tube and Rigid Tubing', 'Culvert Pipes; Culvert Pipe Connector Bands; Metallic Pipes; Plastic Pipes; Tubes and Rigid Tubing and their assemblies.', 'Air Conditioning-Heating Pipes (FSC 4520); Asbestos and Cement, Bituminized Fiber, Clay and Concrete Pipes (FSC 5630); Conduit Pipes and their assemblies (FSC 5975); Downspout Pipes (FSC 5670); Exhaust Pipes (FSC 1560, 2990, and 4520); Fire Extinguishing Systems Pipes and Tubes and their assemblies (FSC 4210); Flexible Tubing (FSC 4720; Glass Tubing (FSC 6640, and 9340); Laboratory Tubes (FSC 6640); Medical and Surgical Tubes (FSC 6515).', null, '47 - PIPE, TUBING, HOSE, AND FITTINGS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4720', 'HOSE AND FLEXIBLE TUBING', '1978-10-15', null, 'Hose and Flexible Tubing', 'Air Duct, Metallic, Nonmetallic, and Textile Fiber Hoses and their assemblies; Flexible Tubing and their assemblies.', 'Conduit and their assemblies (FSC 5975); Laboratory Tubes (FSC 6640); Medical and Surgical Tubes (FSC 6515); Rigid Tubing and their assemblies (FSC 4710).', null, '47 - PIPE, TUBING, HOSE, AND FITTINGS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4730', 'HOSE, PIPE, TUBE, LUBRICATION, AND RAILING FITTINGS', '2011-10-01', null, 'Hose, Pipe, Tube, Lubrication, and Railing Fittings', 'Adapters; Bends; Caps; Clamps; Connectors; Couplings; Crosses; Elbows; Expansion Joints; Ferrules; Flanges; Laterals; Lubrication Fittings; Manifolds; Nipples; Nozzles; Outlets; Plugs; Reducers; Swing and Swivel Joints; Tees; Traps; Unions; Wyes.', 'Air Conditioning-Heating Fittings (FSC 4520); Bituminized Fiber and Concrete Fittings (FSC 5630); Conduit Boxes and Fittings (FSC 5975); Downspout Fittings (FSC 5670); Medical and Surgical Fittings (FSC 6515); Laboratory Fittings (FSC 6640); Post Caps and Rail Ends (FSC 5660); Machine Thread Bushings and Plugs (FSC 5365).', null, '47 - PIPE, TUBING, HOSE, AND FITTINGS', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('48', 'VALVES', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, 'This group excludes valves designed for use on individual types of equipment or systems. Excluded are such items as tire valves, engine intake and exhaust valves, carburetor valves, water mixing valves, and flush valves.', null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4810', 'VALVES, POWERED', '1978-10-15', null, 'Valves, Powered', 'Electric Motor Operated Valves; Hydraulic Operated Valves; Solenoid Operated Valves.', 'Engine Intake and Exhaust valves;(FSC 2990, 2815); Valves specifically designed for use with fire fighting equipment,(FSC 4210); plumbing equipment, and the like (FSC 4540).', null, '48 - VALVES', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4820', 'VALVES, NONPOWERED', '1978-10-15', null, 'Valves, Nonpowered', 'Automatic Nonpowered Valves; Gate, Globe, Angle, Check, and Relief Valves; Cocks.', 'Fire Hydrants (FSC 4210) Sprinkler Heads (FSC 4210); Valves specifically designed for use with fire fighting equipment (FSC 4210); plumbing equipment and the like (FSC 4540)', null, '48 - VALVES', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('49', 'MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', '1979-10-01', null, null, null, null, 'Specialized equipment which is designed for automotive maintenance and repair and which is also used for the maintenance and repair of nonautomotive vehicles or equipment, will be classified in class 4910. Jigs, fixtures, and templates used in conjunction with maintenance and repair shop specialized equipment are classified in this group. However, jigs, fixtures, and templates used in conjunction with metalworking machinery are classified in group 34. Infrared assemblies, subassemblies, and components specifically designed as test and maintenance specialized equipment are classified in the appropriate classes of this group. Excluded from this group is infrared equipment designed for testing communications and night vision equipment.', null, null, null, null, null, null),
  ('4910', 'MOTOR VEHICLE MAINTENANCE AND REPAIR SHOP SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Motor Vehicle Maintenance and Repair Shop Specialized Equipment', 'Automotive Lifts; Wheel Aligners; Brake Service Equipment; Tire Maintenance and Repair Equipment; Test stands and test equipment specially designed for use with motor vehicles.', 'Hand Tools (FSG 51); Lubrication and Fuel Dispensing Equipment (FSC 4930); Basic types of electrical and electronic test instruments, including those specifically designed, such as ammeters, voltmeters, ohmmeters, multimeters, and similar instruments as shown in the indexes in the FSC (FSC 6625).', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4920', 'AIRCRAFT MAINTENANCE AND REPAIR SHOP SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Aircraft Maintenance and Repair Shop Specialized Equipment', 'Maintenance stands designed for support of aircraft assemblies during repair or overhaul; Test Stands and Test Equipment specially designed for maintenance and repair of aircraft components such as: engines, generators, hydraulic systems, armament, automatic pilot, fire control, flight control and navigational systems.', 'Hand Tools; Airfield Maintenance Platforms; Basic types of electrical and electronic test instruments, including those specially designed, such as ammeters, voltmeters, ohmmeters, multimeters, and similar instruments, as shown in the indexes to the FSC; Test Apparatus used for both communications and other electrical and electronic equipment.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4921', 'TORPEDO MAINTENANCE, REPAIR, AND CHECKOUT SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Torpedo Maintenance, Repair, and Checkout Specialized Equipment', 'Specially designed maintenance, test, checkout, and repair shop specialized equipment for maintenance and repair of torpedoes, torpedo components; adapters, fixtures, inspection and holding fixtures, leveling jack assemblies, fuel filling and syphon assemblies control surface adapter and protractor assemblies, afterbody cradle adapter and tilting mount assemblies, high pressure air heater assemblies, motor drier and puller assemblies, test stand levels and stands for overhaul, maintenance, test, checkout, and repair of torpedo and torpedo components, test panels, fixtures, and test sets for electrical circuits, firing circuits and torpedo test sets.', 'Specially designed maintenance test, checkout and repair shop specialized equipment for maintenance and repair of ammunition, guided missiles, rockets, fire control, space vehicles, underwater mines, depth charges and nuclear ordnance. Also excludes "basic" types of electrical and electronic test instruments, such as ammeters, voltmeters, ohmmeters, multimeters, galvanometers and similar instruments.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4923', 'DEPTH CHARGES AND UNDERWATER MINES MAINTENANCE, REPAIR, AND CHECKOUT SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Depth Charges and Underwater Mines Maintenance, Repair, and, Checkout Specialized Equipment', 'Specially designed maintenance, test, checkout and repair shop specialized equipment for maintenance and repair of depth charges and underwater mines; adapters, inspection, test and holding fixtures; stands for overhaul, maintenance, test, checkout, and repair of underwater mines and depth charges; test fixtures, panels plus assemblies and test sets for leak test, pressure test, firing circuits and timing devices.', 'Specially designed maintenance, test, checkout, and repair shop equipment designed for nuclear ordnance, guided missiles, ammunition, torpedoes, rockets, fire control, space vehicles and "basic" types of electrical and electronic test instruments.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4925', 'AMMUNITION MAINTENANCE, REPAIR, AND CHECKOUT SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Ammunition Maintenance, Repair, and Checkout Specialized Equipment', 'Specially designed maintenance, test, checkout, and repair shop specialized equipment, for maintenance and repair of ammunition items; adapters; ammunition feeders and hoppers; inspection and holding fixtures; linkers, linkers-delinkers, and delinkers to assemble and disassemble ammunition belts; surveillance ovens; explosimeters; primer firing device fixtures; mandrels; repositioning machines; gas bomb service kits; test fixtures; panels; plug assemblies; and test sets for ammunition maintenance, checkout, and repair.', 'Maintenance, repair, checkout and test equipment specially designed for use with guided missiles, guided missile remote control systems, guided missile systems; fire control; nuclear ordnance; rockets, underwater mines and depth charges; torpedoes; space vehicles and test equipment for aircraft weapon launchers; basic types of electrical and electronic test instruments, such as ammeters, voltmeters, ohmmeters, multimeters, and similar instruments as shown in the indexes to the FSC.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4927', 'ROCKET MAINTENANCE, REPAIR AND CHECKOUT SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Rocket Maintenance, Repair and Checkout Specialized Equipment', 'Specially designed maintenance, test, checkout, and repair shop specialized equipment for maintenance and repair of rockets and rocket components; rocket maintenance stands; test stands; fixtures; jigs; and shop equipment designed for maintenance and repair of rockets, rocket motors and other rocket components.', 'Specially designed maintenance, test, checkout, and repair shop equipment specifically designed for nuclear ordnance, guided missiles, fire control, torpedoes, underwater mines, depth charges, ammunition, space vehicles; test equipment for aircraft rocket launchers and "basic" types of electrical and electronic test instruments, such as ammeters, voltmeters, ohmmeters, multimeters, galvanometers and similar instruments.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4930', 'LUBRICATION AND FUEL DISPENSING EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Lubrication and Fuel Dispensing Equipment', 'Hand Grease Guns; Centralized Lubrication Systems; Hydrostatic Lubricators; Oil and Gasoline Dispensing Pumps; Fuel Oil Dispensing Pumps; Hand Oilers; Grease Dispensers; Pressure Gun Attachments; Sight Feed Lubricators.', 'Alemite and Lubrication Fittings (FSC 4730).', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4931', 'FIRE CONTROL MAINTENANCE AND REPAIR SHOP SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Fire Control Maintenance and Repair Shop Specialized Equipment', 'Specially Designed Test Equipment, Maintenance Fixtures and Stands.', 'Instruments for use on both Fire Control and other Equipment; Airborne Fire Control Maintenance and Repair Shop Equipment.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4933', 'WEAPONS MAINTENANCE AND REPAIR SHOP SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Weapons Maintenance and Repair Shop Specialized Equipment', 'Maintenance Stands, Fixtures, and Jigs.', 'Atomic Ordnance Maintenance and Repair Shop Specialized Equipment; Airborne Weapons Maintenance and Repair Shop Equipment.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4935', 'GUIDED MISSILE MAINTENANCE, REPAIR, AND CHECKOUT SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Guided Missile Maintenance, Repair, and Checkout Specialized Equipment', 'Checkout equipment and test equipment specially designed for use with guided missiles and guided missile remote control systems.', 'Specially designed internal (built-in) checkout equipment for guided missile remote control systems; Basic types of electrical and electronic test instruments, including those specially designed, such as ammeters, voltmeters, ohmmeters, multimeters, and similar instruments, as shown in the indexes to the FSC; Test Apparatus used for both communications and other electrical and electronic equipment.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4940', 'MISCELLANEOUS MAINTENANCE AND REPAIR SHOP SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Miscellaneous Maintenance and Repair Shop Specialized Equipment', 'Paint Spraying Equipment.', 'Hand Tools (FSG 51).', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4960', 'SPACE VEHICLE MAINTENANCE, REPAIR, AND CHECKOUT SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Space Vehicle Maintenance, Repair, and Checkout Specialized Equipment', 'Checkout and Test Equipment specially designed for use with Space Vehicles, including Remote Control Systems.', 'Checkout and Test Equipment used with both Guided Missiles and Space Vehicles; Specially designed Internal (built-in) Checkout Equipment for Remote Control Systems; Basic types of Electrical and Electronic Test Instruments, including those specially designed, such as ammeters, ohmmeters, multimeters, and similar instruments, as shown in the indexes to the FSC.', null, '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
  ('4970', 'MULTIPLE GUIDED WEAPONS, SPECIALIZED MAINTENANCE AND REPAIR SHOP EQUIPMENT', '2011-10-01', null, 'Multiple Guided Weapons, Specialized Maintenance and Repair Shop Equipment', null, null, 'Maintenance, test, checkout and repair shop equipment designed to test, maintain, fault isolate and repair multiple guided weapon systems. For equipment designed to be used with only one specific system see the individual FSC indexed (i.e. 4921, 4927, 4935).', '49 - MAINT/REPAIR SHOP EQPT', null, '5.0', 'Industrial Products & Services', '5.1', 'Machinery & Components'),
